  "response": "As the world's largest developing country and the most populous nation on the planet, the importance of the Chinese language is self-evident. It is not only the official language of China but also serves as a medium for cultural exchange and a bridge connecting people from all around the world. The Chinese language carries a rich historical depth and cultural significance, representing the wisdom and cultural heritage of the Chinese nation. With China's economic rise and the increasing strength of its comprehensive national power, Chinese has become one of the most widely spoken languages globally, possessing immense practical value and strategic significance. The Chinese government has been actively promoting international Chinese education, encouraging people from all over the world to learn Chinese, and fostering cultural exchanges and cooperation between China and other nations. This further highlights the international influence and importance of the Chinese language.",
